terrform apply actions 
   it will lock the statefile to avoiid concurrent builds 
   it will check the syntax and validates configuration files as per terraform schema 
   terraform downloads the neccessary providers
   terraform compares the latest config file and compare with state file and apply the changes to infrastructure
   it will create a create ,update and delete process for each resources
   terraform will update the statefile to reflect the changes in real infra 
   it will release the statelock 
components required to isolate the containers in docker 
   namespaces and cgroups
cloudtrail logs to identify the api calls in your AWS resources 

   
